    "narrative": "For April 13, 2026, the lineup is anchored by **Corbin Carroll**, who stands as our clear elite play with a score of 85.64. The combination of an optimal #2 spot and favorable wind conditions creates an ideal ceiling for him to exploit the base paths. Meanwhile, the mid-tier of our lineup gets a massive boost from the Yusei Kikuchi matchup. Both **Jose Caballero** (67.93) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (66.92) are high-value starts today, as the soft-tossing lefty provides a prime environment for **Jose Caballero**\u2019s speed to shine and **Giancarlo Stanton**\u2019s power to bridge the gap in our HR and RBI targets. **Gabriel Moreno** also slots in as a high-floor play at 67.29, bolstered by a park-factor boost that elevates his status despite the reliance on projected lineup placement.\n\nWe are forced to navigate significant risks today, most notably the clash between **James Wood** (50.12) and Paul Skenes. While **James Wood** receives a modest score, the 19% downgrade due to Skenes' elite skill makes this a high-variance spot. Similarly, **Seiya Suzuki** (49.57) faces a difficult test against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez, with the opposing catcher\u2019s elite pop time acting as a drag on his stolen base potential. The most difficult bench decision was **Max Muncy**, who finished with a 43.60. While he benefits from the hitting environment against Nathan Eovaldi, the optimizer preferred the superior matchup context of **Tyler Soderstrom** (55.72) and **Alex Freeland** (52.91), relegating **Max Muncy** to the bench to preserve our limited weekly game caps for higher-probability outcomes. With many of our prospects like **Carson Williams** and **Travis Bazzana** waiting in the wings, maintaining discipline in our daily roster construction remains paramount to keeping our 5x5 pace competitive.",
